---++ About this Document

This page serves as index for frequently used security pages.

---++ URGENT 
   * [[Documentation.IncidentDiscoveryReporting][Incident Discovery and Reporting]] - What to do when you discover a potential security problem


---++ Welcome to OSG Security
   * [[Security.GoalsPurpose][Goals and purpose]] of the Security Team
   * [[Documentation.OsgFaq#Security_and_Certificates][Security and certificates FAQ]] 
   * [[Documentation.PoliciesProcedures][Policies and procedures]] - Consolidates security policies important within the OSG
   * [[http://osgsec.blogspot.com/][OSG Security Team Blog]] - Latest notifications and announcements from the security team
   * [[Security.SecurityTeamMembers][Team members]] - OSG Security Team
   * [[Security.EmailLists][Email lists]] - How to contact us when you have questions or wish to report problems
   * [[Documentation.SecureEmail][Secure Email]] - How to send secure emails


---++ Security Awareness for OSG Participants
   * [[Documentation.SecurityAwarenessForTheOSG][Security Awareness]] - OSG Security in a Nutshell
   * [[Documentation.SecurityUserResponsibilities][User Responsibilities]] - The Users' Responsibilities Regarding Security on OSG
   * [[Documentation.SecuritySiteResponsibilities][Site Responsibilities]] - The Sites' Responsibilities Regarding Security on OSG
   * Documentation.PoliciesProcedures - Document consolidates security policies important within the OSG and related organization

---++Certificates
   * [[Documentation.CaDistribution][OSG CA Distribution]] - Information on the OSG Certificate Authority distribution
   * [[Documentation.Release3.InstallCertAuth][CA Certificate Installation and Update]] - Provides you with details of various options to install the Certificate Authority (CA) certificates and have up-to-date certificate revocation list (CRL). 
   * [[http://idmanager.opensciencegrid.org/][OSG Registration Authority]] 
   * [[Documentation.Release3.InstallCertScripts][Certificate Scripts package]] - Documents the cert-scripts package that provides a command-line interface to the DOEGrids CA website and some additional utilities for dealing with X509 certificates.
   * [[Documentation.Release3.CertificateUserGet][How do I get a X.509 Personal Certificate from the OSG CA?]]
      * [[Documentation.CertificateGetWeb][Get a X.509 Personal Certificate using the web]]  
   * How do I get a X.509 Service and Host Certificate from the OSG CA?
      * [[Documentation.Release3.GetHostServiceCertificates][Using command line client]]
      * [[Documentation.Release3.GetHostServiceCertificatesWeb][Using web interface]]
   * Documentation.CertificateRevoke - Steps to take if you need to revoke a certificate

---++ Incidents
   * Documentation.IncidentDiscoveryReporting - Describes the process of reporting a security incident to the OSG Security Team.
   * Documentation.IncidentFirstSteps - Documents first steps one can take when looking into an incident *AFTER* the incident has already been reported. 
   * Documentation.RespondToSecurityRequests - Covers information on how sites can respond to security incidents. 
   * Documentation.ReportRespondToSecurityIncidents - Help for security contacts and administrators report and respond to security incidents at their sites. 

---++ Security Best Practices
   * [[Documentation.SecurityBestPractices][Security Best Practices]] - Documents security practices recommended by the OSG Security Team.
   * [[Documentation.SecurityRisksCE][Security risks on the CE]] - Covers what security risk is, and how that applies to the different aspects of the OSG. 
   * [[Documentation.Release3.BanningUsersAtSite][How to ban a user at a site]] - Describes the different methods of how to ban users in OSG whether sites are using GUMS or gridmap files for authorization. 
   * Documentation.SshHostsAllow - Covers how site administrators can configure their hosts.allow and hosts.deny files to limit the outside locations that can connect to their site with SSH. 
   * Documentation.MaintainVOInformation - Describes how sites can keep the pertinent user authorization information up-to-date at their site.
   * Documentation.BasicForensics - Covers some basic steps one can take to get started when investigating an incident on a machine used in the OSG.
   * Documentation.ApplySecurityUpdates - Document describes the notification process and shows examples for updating the VDT/OSG software. 

---++ Pre Release3 References 
   * ReleaseDocumentation.ValidateVoAccess - Provides information necessary to determine if your gatekeeper is configured to support all VOs and users that you intend to support
   * Trash.ReleaseDocumentationCaCertificatesInstall - Contains the procedure to install certificates from Certificate Authorities recognized by the Open Science Grid. 
   * ReleaseDocumentation.CaCertificatesUpdates - Document locates in one page all of the information for installation of the CA certificate updating process. 
   * ReleaseDocumentation.MaintainCAInformation - Describes the importance of keeping the CA information at sites up-to-date and then covers the scripts and process for implementing it on machines. 

---++!! Comments
